Patch Set 4:

Hi James,

All the TBF commands I can think of are passed now.

However, following script got failure of "cat: /proc/fs/lustre/ost/OSS/ost_io/nrs_tbf_rule: No space left on device". It is not a problem of this patch, since the old codes have similar problem too. I am wondering whether there is any easy to fix it based on seq_files? We really don't want to limit the rule number we can define.

NUMBER=84
for((i=0;i<$NUMBER;i++)){
    echo -n start xixi_$i {0@lo} 1 > /proc/fs/lustre/ost/OSS/ost_io/nrs_tbf_rule;
}
cat /proc/fs/lustre/ost/OSS/ost_io/nrs_tbf_rule;
